From Gordon Banks Subject Re eye dominance In article Richard Silver writes Is there a right eye dominance eyedness as there is an overall right handedness in the population I mean do most people require less lens corrections for the one eye than the other If so what kinds of percentages can be attached to this There is eye dominance same as handedness and usually for the same side It has nothing to do with refractive error Gordon Banks Skepticism is the chastity of the intellect and it is shameful to surrender it too